[31m-# zmk-nodefree-config[m
[31m-[m
[31m-ZMK lets user customize their keyboard layout by providing a Devicetree file[m
[31m-(`.keymap`). The specific syntax requirements of the Devicetree file format can,[m
[31m-however, make this process a bit daunting for new users. [m
[31m-[m
[31m-This repository provides simple convenience macros that simplify the configuration for[m
[31m-many common use cases. It results in a "node-free" user configuration with a more[m
[31m-streamlined syntax. Check out [example.keymap](example.keymap) to see it in action.[m
[31m-[m
[31m-See [changelog](#changelog) for latest changes.[m
[31m-[m
[31m-## Overview[m
[31m-[m
[31m-The following convenience macros are provided:[m
[31m-1. `ZMK_BEHAVIOR` creates behaviors such as hold-taps, tap-dances or[m
[31m-   ZMK macros [\[doc\]](#zmk_behavior)[m
[31m-2. `ZMK_LAYER` adds layers to the keymap [\[doc\]](#zmk_layer)[m
[31m-3. `ZMK_COMBO` defines combos [\[doc\]](#zmk_combo)[m
[31m-4. `ZMK_CONDITIONAL_LAYER` sets up "tri-layer" conditions [\[doc\]](#zmk_conditional_layer)[m
[31m-5. `ZMK_UNICODE_SINGLE` and `ZMK_UNICODE_PAIR` create unicode characters [\[doc\]](#zmk_unicode)[m
[31m-6. `international_chars` provides character definitions for some non-English languages[m
[31m-   [\[doc\]](#international-characters)[m
[31m-7. `keypos_def` provides human-readable key position shortcuts for some popular[m
[31m-   keyboards that simplify the configuration of combos and positional hold-taps[m
[31m-   [\[doc\]](#key-position-helpers)[m
[31m-[m
