[31m-### Key-position helpers[m
[31m-[m
[31m-Certain configuration options such as combos and positional hold-taps are based on the[m
[31m-physical position of keys on the keyboard. This can be cumbersome and reduces[m
[31m-portability of configuration files across keyboards with different layouts. [m
[31m-[m
[31m-To increase portability and ease of use, this repo provides optional key-position[m
[31m-helpers for some popular keyboard layouts (58-key boards such as Lily58, 48-key boards[m
[31m-such as Planck, 42-key boards such as Corne, 36-key boards and 34-key boards).[m
[31m-[m
[31m-These key-position helpers provide a map from the physical key positions to human-readable shortcuts.[m
[31m-All shortcuts are of the following form:[m
[31m-* `L/R` for **L**eft/**R**ight hand[m
[31m-* `T/M/B/H` for **T**op/**M**iddle/**B**ottom and t**H**umb row.[m
[31m-* `0/1/2/3/4` for the finger position starting from the inside (`0` is the inner[m
[31m-  index-finger column, `1` is the home position of the index finger, ..., `4` is the home[m
[31m-  position of the pinkie)[m
[31m-[m
[31m-For instance, the shortcuts layout for a 36-key board looks as follows:[m
[31m-```[m
[31m-╭─────────────────────┬─────────────────────╮[m
[31m-│ LT4 LT3 LT2 LT1 LT0 │ RT0 RT1 RT2 RT3 RT4 │[m
[31m-│ LM4 LM3 LM2 LM1 LM0 │ RM0 RM1 RM2 RM3 RM4 │[m
[31m-│ LB4 LB3 LB2 LB1 LB0 │ RB0 RB1 RB2 RB3 RB4 │[m
[31m-╰───────╮ LH2 LH1 LH0 │ RH0 RH1 RH2 ╭───────╯[m
[31m-        ╰─────────────┴─────────────╯[m
[31m-```[m
[31m-Schematics for all supported keyboards can be found in the corresponding[m
[31m-definition files in the `keypos_def` folder.[m
[31m-[m
[31m-To use these key-position helpers, source the definition file for your keyboard[m
[31m-into your `.keymap` file. E.g., for a 36-key board, use:[m
[31m-```C++[m
[31m-#include "../zmk-nodefree-config/keypos_def/keypos_36keys.h"[m
[31m-```[m
[31m-[m
[31m-#### Example 1: Defining combos using key-position helpers[m
[31m-[m
[31m-```C++[m
[31m-ZMK_COMBO(copy,  &kp LC(C), LB2 LB3, ALL)[m
[31m-ZMK_COMBO(paste, &kp LC(V), LB1 LB2, ALL)[m
[31m-```[m
[31m-[m
[31m-This defines a "copy"-combo for the middle + ring finger on the left bottom row, and a[m
[31m-"paste"-combo for the index + middle finger on the left bottom row. Both combos are active on all layers.[m
[31m-[m
[31m-#### Example 2: Home-row mods with positional hold-taps[m
[31m-[m
[31m-Here we use ZMK's [positional[m
[31m-hold-tap](https://zmk.dev/docs/behaviors/hold-tap#positional-hold-tap-and-hold-trigger-key-positions)[m
[31m-feature to make home-row mods only trigger with "opposite hand" keys. Using[m
[31m-key-position helpers makes this straightforward: [m
[31m-[m
[31m-```C++[m
[31m-#define KEYS_L LT0 LT1 LT2 LT3 LT4 LM0 LM1 LM2 LM3 LM4 LB0 LB1 LB2 LB3 LB4  // left-hand keys[m
[31m-#define KEYS_R RT0 RT1 RT2 RT3 RT4 RM0 RM1 RM2 RM3 RM4 RB0 RB1 RB2 RB3 RB4  // right-hand keys[m
[31m-#define THUMBS LH2 LH1 LH0 RH0 RH1 RH2                                      // thumb keys[m
[31m-[m
[31m-ZMK_BEHAVIOR(hml, hold_tap,  // left-hand HRMs[m
[31m-    flavor = "balanced";[m
[31m-    tapping-term-ms = <280>;[m
[31m-    quick-tap-ms = <125>;[m
[31m-    global-quick-tap;[m
[31m-    bindings = <&kp>, <&kp>;[m
[31m-    hold-trigger-key-positions = <KEYS_R THUMBS>;[m
[31m-)[m
[31m-[m
[31m-ZMK_BEHAVIOR(hmr, hold_tap,  // right-hand HRMs[m
[31m-    flavor = "balanced";[m
[31m-    tapping-term-ms = <280>;[m
[31m-    quick-tap-ms = <125>;[m
[31m-    global-quick-tap;[m
[31m-    bindings = <&kp>, <&kp>;[m
[31m-    hold-trigger-key-positions = <KEYS_L THUMBS>;[m
[31m-)[m
[31m-```[m
